<div class="service-page rc-fade">
    <div class="faq-hero">
        <p class="section__text__p1">Cognitive Systems</p>
        <h1 class="title">Healthcare AI Integration</h1>
        <p class="faq-hero-sub">Securely bringing the power of Generative AI and Machine Learning to your medical practice or health-tech startup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section-container" style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem;">
        <div class="text-container">
            <h2>Intelligent Automation with Guardrails</h2>
            <p>
                Artificial Intelligence is transforming healthcare, but it requires rigorous implementation to ensure patient data privacy and clinical safety. I build AI features that are secure, interpretable, and strictly scoped to assist—not replace—human judgment.
            </p>
            
            <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: var(--c);">AI Capabilities</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Clinical Document Analysis:</strong> Intelligent extraction of structured data from unstructured medical records and intake forms.</li>
                <li><strong>RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation):</strong> Chatbots and search interfaces that ground their answers exclusively in your proprietary medical knowledge bases and guidelines.</li>
                <li><strong>Workflow Automation:</strong> Automating repetitive administrative tasks, such as coding assistance and appointment triaging, to reduce provider burnout.</li>
                <li><strong>HIPAA-Eligible LLM Integration:</strong> Deploying private models or using business-tier APIs (Azure OpenAI, AWS Bedrock) that guarantee zero data retention for training.</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="rc-cta-box rc-glass" style="margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; text-align: center;">
                <h3>Ready to leverage AI safely?</h3>
                <a href="/#quote" class="btn btn-outline-dark" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Let's Explore AI Use Cases</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
